We want to ensure everyone enjoys a safe experience when visiting our Fitness Center. Basically, just use common sense. We're here to answer any questions. Work out and stay safe!

With the Fitness Center is in hibernation mode, it's time to head outside! But safely!
Yes, you can go outside and it is HIGHLY encouraged.
Just remember: 1) Don't go out if you feel sick 2) Stay 6ft away from others 3) Don't play on play ground equipment. 4) Don't visit busy or common areas (grocery stores, gas stations)

Get outside, go for a walk. Play basketball with your family. Go on a hike. Go fishing. It's probably the best medicine you can get.

post_text:
Stockton Recreation will be cancelling all youth activities for the remainder of the school calendar, May 15, 2020.

As to what we do know:
1) Soccer registrations who have paid will be contacted regarding refunds on payments in the coming weeks.
2) All youth classes and activities will be cancelled.
3) Summer registrations for baseball and softball will be postponed. We will reevaluate at a later date.

What we will determine:
1) The offering of Adult Activities during the spring and summer months.
2) Keeping the SRC Fitness Center open. This is a day to day decision. At this point, we will continue to operate under the CDC recommendation of no more than 10 people in the building with regular cleaning and disinfecting. If the decision is made to close the facility for a period of time, those with active memberships will have their memberships adjusted accordingly.

Yesterday was International Women's Day, but honestly, we should be lifting up women every day. Tell the women in your life how important they are. Then show it.

Women, let's empower each other. Let's exercise. Let's exercise positivity by not tearing each other down. Let's exercise inclusiveness by bringing other women into the fold. And, of course, let's exercise our bodies. Invite others to workout with you. Find a walking/running partner. Teach a gal pal to lift. Strong women help make others strong.

post_text:
🥯🥞🥮🍧🍰🎂🍩🍦Biggest Challenge #5 Sugar Free Weekend🚫🚫🚫🚫🚫
Sugar. Is. Everywhere. And it's not good for you. (Surprise!) Like this bad for you--->https://www.health.harvard.edu/heart-health/the-sweet-danger-of-sugar
So we're doing a short, sugar detox. No added, processed sugar. So obviously no sweet stuff. But what about pasta sauce? Pickles? Cheezits? Look on the label. If it has 'sugar' or any one of its many named cousins in the ingredients list, you can't eat it. Once you start looking at labels you're going to find sugar lurks where it shouldn't . Look here--->https://www.consumerreports.org/cro/2012/05/where-sugar-hides-and-how-to-eat-less/index.htm

So eat fresh. Minimally processed food. Whole. You know the drill. Saturday and Sunday. Good Luck!

And if any non- Biggest Winner members want to try, share your story!

Stockton Recreation Commission and Fitness Center
November 19, 2019 at 3:46 PM ·

It's that time of year. If you are unwell and exhibit fever, chills, aches, nausea, diarrhea, please stay home!

Remember to clean/disinfect equipment/machines when you conclude your workout. It is your responsibility and expected. This keeps the machines clean for the next user and helps eliminate those nasty germs.

post_text: 🏋️‍♀️⛹️‍♀️🚴‍♀️🏃‍♂️Get to moving! Challenge #3 for Biggest Winner 20/20 participants is all about getting your daily exercise in. Cardio exercise. Walking, running, aerobic activity, biking, basketball. Something that gets your heart rate up for at least 30 minutes. Lifting weights is great, just add it to your 30 minutes of cardio. Participants need 30 minutes, 4 days/week. They have Tuesday-Sunday to get it in. And, surprise, you CAN workout on Super Bowl Sunday.

post_text:
We're knee deep in our Biggest Winner 20/20. Now to start some challenges to help develop some good habits. (And to make things interesting) We invite you to do it along with us. You won't win a prize but you sure may feel better.

This week. 2 out of your 3 meals MUST include a serving of veggies and fruit. No, they can't be fries (or potatoes for that matter). So add some broccoli, green beans, salad, apples, bananas, blueberries, or strawberries to your meal. Maybe dragon fruit if you're adventurous. On the side is fine. Be better to replace something. Fresh or frozen is best. Not fried (duh).

🍏🍎🍐🍊🍋🍌🍉🍇🍓🍈🍒🍑🥭🥭🍍🥥🥝🌽🌶🥒🥬🥦🥑🍆🍅🥕🍠🥗
So hit the produce aisle.
